{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"35a03097-c6db-405a-bcdb-6e4dd9cf8cfe","content":"Here's the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform on .NET 8:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- \\\n  --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage \\\n  --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump \\\n  --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Key differences:**\n\n| VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|--------|---------------------------|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\nThe `--` separator is required with .NET 8's `dotnet test` to forward args to the new platform. You'll also need these packages in your test project:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump\" />\n```\n\n> **Note:** .NET 9+ SDK has native `dotnet test` integration with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, removing the need for `--`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"95e43c0e-13d3-4df6-b143-0eb5fd680927","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. They want to know what the equivalent command should look like.\n\nLet me provide the equivalent command. Microsoft.Testing.Platform uses a different CLI syntax:\n\n- `--filter` → `--filter` (same)\n- `--logger trx` → `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura`\n- `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`\n\n\n- `--blame-hang` → `--hangdump`\n- `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` → `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform, you can run tests either directly as an executable or through `dotnet test`, though the argument syntax differs slightly depending on which approach you use.\n\nIn .NET 8 with the new platform, several common test arguments have been renamed: `--filter` remains the same but there's also `--treenode-filter` for the new syntax, `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`, `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` simplifies to `--coverage`, and `--blame-crash` maps to `--crashdump`. For coverage output in cobertura format, you'd use `--coverage-output-format cobertura`. So with Microsoft.Testing.Platform on .NET 8, I need to clarify the two approaches: either running the test executable directly or using `dotnet test` with the MSBuild integration package to forward arguments. The command structure differs slightly depending on which method they're using—arguments go after `--` when using `dotnet test`, or directly to the executable when running it standalone.","outputTokens":1258,"requestId":"E3C4:3454B1:1F0EC55:2206B52:6A05200E"},"id":"f2f7c7bf-b0f4-4ce6-86aa-a21fa7e0bb23","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:06:43.179Z","parentId":"44707014-3365-4b9b-a89b-a6f1dd98b4eb"}
